\section{Introduction}
\label{sec:introduction}

\subsection{Purpose}
This document outlines the software requirements for \textbf{Pick My Dish}, a Flutter-based mobile application that provides personalized recipe recommendations based on user preferences, ingredients, cooking time, and mood. It serves as a comprehensive guide for developers, testers, project managers, and stakeholders.

\subsection{Scope}
\textbf{Pick My Dish} is a cross-platform mobile application that allows users to:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Browse, search, and filter recipes.
    \item Upload, edit, and delete their own recipes.
    \item Personalize recipe recommendations based on ingredients, cooking time, and emotions.
    \item Mark recipes as favorites.
    \item Manage user profiles with profile pictures and usernames.
    \item View detailed recipe instructions, ingredients, and nutritional information.
\end{itemize}

The system interfaces with a RESTful backend server (Node.js + MySQL) for data storage and retrieval. The app is developed using \textbf{Flutter} and follows the \textbf{MVVM architecture} with \textbf{Provider} for state management.

\subsection{Definitions, Acronyms, and Abbreviations}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lY}
        \toprule
        \textbf{Term} & \textbf{Description} \\
        \midrule
        API & Application Programming Interface \\
        UI & User Interface \\
        SRS & Software Requirements Specification \\
        MVVM & Model-View-ViewModel \\
        JWT & JSON Web Token (for authentication) \\
        VPS & Virtual Private Server \\
        SQLite & Local database for offline storage \\
        HTTP & Hypertext Transfer Protocol \\
        FR & Functional Requirement \\
        NFR & Non-Functional Requirement \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{Definitions and Acronyms}
\end{table}

\subsection{References}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Flutter Documentation: \url{https://flutter.dev}
    \item Provider Package: \url{https://pub.dev/packages/provider}
    \item REST API Design Guidelines
    \item Project Source Code Documentation
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Overview}
This document is structured into sections that describe:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Overall system functionality
    \item User roles and characteristics
    \item Functional and non-functional requirements
    \item Interface requirements
    \item Constraints and assumptions
\end{itemize}

\newpage

\section{Overall Description}
\label{sec:overall-description}

\subsection{Product Perspective}
\textbf{Pick My Dish} is an independent mobile application that communicates with a backend server hosted on a VPS. The app is built using \textbf{Flutter} for cross-platform compatibility (iOS \& Android). It uses \textbf{SQLite} for local caching and \textbf{HTTP} for server communication.

\begin{figure}[H]
    \centering
    \includegraphics[width=0.8\textwidth]{system-architecture.png}
    \caption{System Architecture Overview}
    \label{fig:system-architecture}
\end{figure}

\subsection{Product Functions}
The primary functions of the system include:
\begin{enumerate}
    \item \textbf{User Authentication}: Register, login, and guest access.
    \item \textbf{Recipe Management}: Browse, search, filter, upload, edit, and delete recipes.
    \item \textbf{Personalization}: Generate recipe recommendations based on selected ingredients, cooking time, and mood.
    \item \textbf{Favorites Management}: Add/remove recipes to/from favorites.
    \item \textbf{User Profile Management}: Update username and profile picture.
    \item \textbf{Admin Features}: Edit/delete any recipe (admin role).
    \item \textbf{Offline Access}: Cached recipes and images for offline viewing.
\end{enumerate}

\subsection{User Characteristics}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lY}
        \toprule
        \textbf{User Type} & \textbf{Description} \\
        \midrule
        End Users & Home cooks, cooking enthusiasts, beginners. Regular users who browse, cook, and share recipes. \\
        Admin Users & Content moderators or administrators with extended privileges to manage all recipes and users. \\
        Guests & Users without an account. Have limited access to browse recipes but cannot save favorites or upload recipes. \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{User Characteristics}
\end{table}

\subsection{Constraints}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Must support \textbf{iOS 12+} and \textbf{Android 8.0+}.
    \item Backend server must be reachable via public IP.
    \item Maximum image upload size: \textbf{5 MB}.
    \item Must comply with GDPR for user data (if applicable).
    \item Development must follow Flutter best practices and Dart style guide.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Assumptions and Dependencies}
\begin{itemize}
    \item Users have a stable internet connection for real-time data sync.
    \item Backend server is maintained and available with 99\% uptime.
    \item Users have basic familiarity with mobile applications.
    \item The app will be distributed via Google Play Store and Apple App Store.
    \item Third-party packages used are maintained and compatible with Flutter updates.
\end{itemize}

\newpage

\section{System Features and Requirements}
\label{sec:system-features}

\subsection{Functional Requirements}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lYc}
        \toprule
        \textbf{ID} & \textbf{Requirement Description} & \textbf{Priority} \\
        \midrule
        FR1 & Users can register with email, username, and password with validation & High \\
        FR2 & Users can log in with email/password or as guest & High \\
        FR3 & Users can view a list of recipes with images, names, and cooking times & High \\
        FR4 & Users can search recipes by name, category, or mood & Medium \\
        FR5 & Users can filter recipes by ingredients, cooking time, and mood & Medium \\
        FR6 & Logged-in users can upload new recipes with image, ingredients, steps, and mood tags & High \\
        FR7 & Recipe owners or admins can edit recipe details & Medium \\
        FR8 & Recipe owners or admins can delete recipes & Medium \\
        FR9 & Users can add/remove recipes to/from favorites & High \\
        FR10 & Users can update username and profile picture & Medium \\
        FR11 & Users can generate personalized recipes based on selected criteria & High \\
        FR12 & Users can view cached recipes without internet connection & Low \\
        FR13 & Admins can edit/delete any recipe & Low \\
        FR14 & System validates email format and password strength during registration & Medium \\
        FR15 & System provides ingredient selector with search and add-new functionality & Medium \\
        FR16 & System caches images for offline viewing & Low \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{Functional Requirements}
\end{table}

\subsection{Non-Functional Requirements}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lY}
        \toprule
        \textbf{ID} & \textbf{Requirement Description} \\
        \midrule
        NFR1 & \textbf{Performance}: App should load recipes within \textbf{2 seconds}. Image caching should reduce bandwidth usage. \\
        NFR2 & \textbf{Usability}: Intuitive UI with consistent navigation, clear icons, and responsive design. \\
        NFR3 & \textbf{Reliability}: 99\% uptime for backend server; graceful error handling with user-friendly messages. \\
        NFR4 & \textbf{Security}: Passwords hashed using bcrypt; JWT for session management; input validation to prevent injection attacks. \\
        NFR5 & \textbf{Compatibility}: Supports Flutter \textbf{3.9+}, iOS 12+, Android 8.0+, various screen sizes and resolutions. \\
        NFR6 & \textbf{Scalability}: Backend supports up to \textbf{10,000 concurrent users} with horizontal scaling capability. \\
        NFR7 & \textbf{Maintainability}: Modular code structure with clear separation of concerns (Models, Providers, Services, Screens). \\
        NFR8 & \textbf{Availability}: System available 24/7 with maintenance windows announced in advance. \\
        NFR9 & \textbf{Portability}: Single codebase runs on both iOS and Android without platform-specific modifications. \\
        NFR10 & \textbf{Testability}: Comprehensive unit and integration test coverage; testable architecture patterns. \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{Non-Functional Requirements}
\end{table}

\newpage

\section{External Interface Requirements}
\label{sec:external-interfaces}

\subsection{User Interfaces}
The application includes the following main screens:
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Splash Screen}: Displays app logo and brief loading animation (3 seconds).
    \item \textbf{Login/Register Screens}: Form-based authentication with validation and password strength indicator.
    \item \textbf{Home Screen}: Personalized recommendations, today's recipes, side menu navigation.
    \item \textbf{Recipe Screens}: List view, grid view, and detailed recipe view with step-by-step instructions.
    \item \textbf{Profile Screen}: User information, edit options, profile picture management, logout.
    \item \textbf{Upload/Edit Screens}: Comprehensive forms for recipe data entry, image picker, and ingredient selector.
    \item \textbf{Favorites Screen}: Grid/list of favorited recipes with swipe-to-remove functionality.
\end{itemize}

\textbf{UI Design Principles}:
\begin{itemize}
    \item Consistent color scheme (black/orange/white)
    \times Times New Roman font family for titles and text
    \item Responsive layouts for various screen sizes
    \item Intuitive navigation with clear visual hierarchy
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Hardware Interfaces}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Camera/Gallery}: For uploading profile and recipe images via \texttt{image\_picker} package.
    \item \textbf{Internet Connectivity}: Wi-Fi or mobile data for API calls and real-time updates.
    \item \textbf{Storage}: Local device storage for caching images and SQLite database.
    \item \textbf{Memory}: Minimum 1GB RAM recommended for smooth operation.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Software Interfaces}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lY}
        \toprule
        \textbf{Component} & \textbf{Description} \\
        \midrule
        Operating System & iOS 12+, Android 8.0+ via Flutter framework \\
        Backend API & RESTful endpoints hosted at \texttt{http://38.242.246.126:3000} (or localhost for development) \\
        Local Database & SQLite for caching recipes and user preferences \\
        Third-Party Libraries & \begin{itemize}[leftmargin=*, nosep]
            \item \texttt{cached\_network\_image}: Image caching
            \item \texttt{image\_picker}: Photo selection
            \item \texttt{http}: API communication
            \item \texttt{provider}: State management
            \item \texttt{sqflite}: SQLite database
            \item \texttt{intl}: Internationalization
            \item \texttt{flutter\_cache\_manager}: Cache management
        \end{itemize} \\
        Development Tools & Flutter SDK, Dart, Android Studio, Xcode \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{Software Interfaces}
\end{table}

\subsection{Communication Interfaces}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Protocol}: HTTP/HTTPS for all client-server communication.
    \item \textbf{Data Format}: JSON for request/response payloads.
    \item \textbf{Authentication}: JWT tokens sent in Authorization header.
    \item \textbf{Error Handling}: Standard HTTP status codes with descriptive error messages.
    \item \textbf{Rate Limiting}: Implemented on server-side to prevent abuse.
\end{itemize}

\newpage

\section{Other Non-Functional Requirements}
\label{sec:other-requirements}

\subsection{Performance Requirements}
\begin{table}[H]
    \centering
    \begin{tabularx}{\textwidth}{lYc}
        \toprule
        \textbf{Metric} & \textbf{Requirement} & \textbf{Target} \\
        \midrule
        App Startup Time & Time from launch to home screen display & < 3 seconds \\
        Recipe List Loading & Time to load and display recipe list & ≤ 2 seconds \\
        Image Loading & Time to load cached images & < 1 second \\
        API Response Time & Server response time for API calls & < 500 ms \\
        Database Operations & Local SQLite read/write operations & < 100 ms \\
        Search Response & Time to filter/search recipes & < 1 second \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabularx}
    \caption{Performance Requirements}
\end{table}

\subsection{Security Requirements}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Authentication}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Password hashing using bcrypt algorithm
        \item JWT token-based authentication with 24-hour expiration
        \item Secure token storage using Flutter Secure Storage
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Authorization}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Role-based access control (User, Admin)
        \item Recipe ownership validation for edit/delete operations
        \item Server-side authorization checks for all protected endpoints
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Data Protection}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item HTTPS for all network communications
        \item Input validation and sanitization
        \item SQL injection prevention via parameterized queries
        \item File upload validation (type, size, virus scanning)
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Privacy}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item GDPR compliance for EU users
        \item Clear privacy policy and data usage terms
        \item User data encryption at rest
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Software Quality Attributes}
\begin{itemize}
    \item \textbf{Maintainability}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Clean architecture with separation of concerns
        \item Comprehensive code documentation
        \item Modular design with reusable components
        \item Consistent coding standards (Dart style guide)
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Testability}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Unit tests for models and services
        \item Integration tests for UI components
        \item Mock server for API testing
        \item Test coverage target: 80\%+
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Portability}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Single codebase for iOS and Android
        \item Responsive design for various screen sizes
        \item Platform-specific adaptations where necessary
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Reliability}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Graceful error handling and recovery
        \item Offline capability with data synchronization
        \item Automatic retry for failed network requests
        \item Comprehensive logging and monitoring
    \end{itemize}
    
    \item \textbf{Usability}:
    \begin{itemize}
        \item Intuitive navigation and workflow
        \item Consistent UI patterns and components
        \item Accessibility features (font scaling, contrast)
        \item Clear error messages and user guidance
    \end{itemize}
\end{itemize}

